TY  - JOUR
AU  - Knyazeva, Anzhela
AU  - Knyazeva, Diana
AU  - Masulis, Ronald W.
T1  - The Supply of Corporate Directors and Board Independence
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hht020
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 26
IS  - 6
SP  - 1561
EP  - 1605
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Empirical evidence on the relations between board independence and board decisions and firm performance is generally confounded by serious endogeneity issues. We circumvent these endogeneity problems by demonstrating the strong impact of the local director labor market on board composition. Specifically, we show that proximity to larger pools of local director talent leads to more independent boards for all but the largest quartile of S&amp;P 1500. Using local director pools as an instrument for board independence, we document that board independence has a positive effect on firm value, operating performance, fraction of CEO incentive-based pay, and CEO turnover.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hht020
ER  - 



